create

public void create()
            throws AppException
Making the new bank account persistent by saving the actual file as .old, set the id, append *this and write all bank accounts.

Throws:
AppException - If an bank account with this nickname exists already, or in case of read or write errors.

remove

public void remove()
            throws AppException
Remove the bank account.

Throws:
AppException - If no bank account entry exists with the given id, or in case of read or write errors.

update

public void update(java.lang.String accountNumber,
                   java.lang.String bankName,
                   java.lang.String nickname,
                   java.lang.String description,
                   java.lang.String bankCode,
                   java.lang.String iban,
                   java.lang.String user)
            throws AppException
Actualize the given account by id in the persistent storage. The date field is set to the actual date and time.

Parameters:
accountNumber - The new bank account number.
bankName - The new long bank name.
nickname - The new short bank name.
description - The new bank entry description.
bankCode - The new bank code (German BLZ).
iban - The new International Bank Account Number.
user - The user, who is changing the entry.
Throws:
AppException - If no entry found with this id, or in case of read or write errors.

getBankAccountNickname

public static java.lang.String getBankAccountNickname(int id)
                                               throws AppException
Returns the short bank name for an BankAccount internal identifier. For the backward compatibility to version 0.1 it gives "?" if the ID is 0 and no bank account exists.

Parameters:
id - The internal bank account identifier.
Returns:
The short bank name.
Throws:
AppException - If no such entry exists or in case of read errors.
